    "body":  "The current design presents both the “How It Works” and “Tips” panels with equal visual weight, which makes it harder for users to distinguish between core process guidance and optional best practices. To improve clarity and guide the user more effectively, we should adjust the layout and styling to create a stronger visual hierarchy.\n\n**Proposed Enhancements:**\n\n1. Hierarchy Adjustment\n\n- Make “How It Works” visually dominant over “Tips” (e.g., bolder/larger header, different background color or border).\n- Consider using a numbered list layout with stronger emphasis to communicate sequential flow.\n\n2. Layout Improvements\n\n- Move the “How It Works” panel to the top of the content section, directly beneath the header and tagline.\n- Keep “Tips” in its current right-aligned box, but visually differentiate it as optional info (e.g., with a lightbulb icon 💡 or a lighter background color).\n\n3. Optional Enhancements\n\n- Add subtle icons for each step in “How It Works” (e.g., 📄 upload, 🤖 AI parse, 📝 review, ✅ save).\n- Allow collapsible/expandable behavior for “Tips” if needed later.\n\n**Rationale:**\nThis change helps guide first-time users by making it immediately clear which section explains the process and which is optional guidance. It improves onboarding and reduces the chance of user confusion or missed steps.",
